    "chemicalDescription": [
      "rh-Polypeptide-105 is a single chain recombinant human peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is directly isolated from a human cell which codes for Growth-Regulated Alpha Protein or C-X-C Motif Chemokine Ligand 1 used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 107 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
